    "description": "I discovered this was an issue while experimenting with the `UnitSystem` machinery. I wanted to be able to write a line like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nus = UnitSystem('custom', 'angstrom', electron_mass, 's', current_mks_unit=elementary_charge)\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrently this fails with a unit parse error because the `Unit` object doesn't do the right thing when it's handed a YTQuantity. Rather than sanitizing the input to `UnitSystem` I figure let's just make the `Unit` class do the right thing when it's handed a YTQuantity.\r\n\r\nThis is a little tricky because I need to avoid a circular import, since `YTArray` needs to be able to import `Unit`. Rather than doing import tricks and using `isinstance`, instead I use `hasattr` to check that whatever we're handed looks sufficiently like a `YTArray`. If reviewers would prefer for me to implement this another way please let me know.\r\n\r\nFinally I also noticed that `UnitSystem` isn't in the API docs, so I've added it.",
